🔹 Loops in Shell
Without Loop
echo "Hello"echo "Hello"echo "Hello"
With Loop
for i in {1..3}do  echo "Hello"done

Types of Loops
LoopUse CaseforFixed number of timeswhileUntil condition is trueuntilUntil condition becomes true

for loop
for i in {1..5}do  echo "Iteration $i"done

while loop
i=1while [ $i -le 5 ]do  echo "Count: $i"  ((i++))done

until loop
i=1until [ $i -gt 5 ]do  echo "Number: $i"  ((i++))done

Use Case: Retry API Calls
for ((i=1; i<=5; i++))do  echo "Attempt $i"  curl -s http://localhost:8080 && break  sleep 2done

🔹 PATH Environment Variable
What is PATH?
Tells Linux where to look for executable commands.
Check PATH
echo $PATH

Add Current Directory to PATH (Temporary)
export PATH=$PATH:$(pwd)

Permanent Setup
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:$(pwd)' >> ~/.bashrcsource ~/.bashrc

🔹 Shell Script to Host Website

#!/bin/bash

PORT=$1

# Create Website folder
mkdir -p website
cd website

# Create Sample HTML file
cat <<EOF > index.html
<html>
<head><title>My Website</title></head>
<body>
<h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
<p>Hosted using shell script</p>
</body>
</html>
EOF

# Start server
echo "Starting Website on Port $PORT"
nohup python3 -m http.server $PORT > server.log 2>&1 &

echo "Website is running at http://13.206.81.151:$PORT"